From Henry Spencer Subject Re Why not give billion to first year lo In article C szvL I writes I'd be inclined to make the prize somewhat larger, but G might be enough this all sounds like that Indecent Proposal movie wouldn't there be a lot of people that would try this with little hope of working just to get the dough if you have a chance and it costs you Mil, then you might pay some stooge a few grand to be your lucky hero just send up a few dozen and is bound to survive enough to make YOU rich Any prize like this is going to need to be worded carefully enough that you cannot get it without demonstrating sustained and reliable capability, rather than a lucky one shot It can be done All work is one man's work Henry Spencer U of Toronto Zoology Kipling utzoo henry